Rainbow orchestrates the following open-source projects. These are not
bundled with Rainbow — they are downloaded and run as separate processes
(Docker containers or native binaries) by the end user. Their licenses
apply to their respective codebases, not to Rainbow.

  Immich — Self-hosted photo/video management
  License: AGPL-3.0
  https://github.com/immich-app/immich

  Stalwart Mail Server — Email, calendar, contacts
  License: AGPL-3.0 / Server-Side Enterprise License v1 (dual)
  https://github.com/stalwartlabs/stalwart

  CryptPad — Collaborative document editing
  License: AGPL-3.0
  https://github.com/cryptpad/cryptpad

  Jellyfin — Media server
  License: GPL-2.0
  https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin

  Seafile — File sync and share
  License: AGPL-3.0 (server), Apache-2.0 (client)
  https://github.com/haiwen/seafile

  Authentik — Identity provider and SSO
  License: MIT
  https://github.com/goauthentik/authentik

  Paper — Minecraft server
  License: GPL-3.0
  https://github.com/PaperMC/Paper

  Caddy — Web server and reverse proxy
  License: Apache-2.0
  https://github.com/caddyserver/caddy

  PostgreSQL — Relational database
  License: PostgreSQL License (BSD-like)
  https://www.postgresql.org/about/licence/

  Valkey — In-memory data store (Redis fork)
  License: BSD-3-Clause
  https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey

  Restic — Encrypted backup tool
  License: BSD-2-Clause
  https://github.com/restic/restic

  cloudflared — Cloudflare Tunnel client
  License: Apache-2.0
  https://github.com/cloudflare/cloudflared

